1. Initialise project on spring initializer and install dependencies as required.
2. Run application -> would show some errors (gotta change application.properties).
3. In application.properties -> add :
	spring.application.name=scm2.0
server.port=8081

#mysql
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/scm20
#datasource url
spring.datasource.username=root
spring.datasource.password=12345 (same as MySQL password as given during installation)

#email configuration

4. Run the app and then run the sql eorkbench -> you can see the database on port 3306
5. give password and create schema -> name same as your schema - scm20
now its runnin on tomcat
